  <front>
    <title>Storing certificates in DNS for email applications</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-schlyter-mailcert-dns-00"/>
    <author initials="J." surname="Schlyter" fullname="Jacob Schlyter"/>
    <author initials="S." surname="Josefsson" fullname="Simon Josefsson">
      <organization>RSA Security</organization>
    </author>
    <author initials="R." surname="Arends" fullname="Roy Arends">
      <organization>Nominum</organization>
    </author>
    <date day="13" month="November" year="2001"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>The Domain Name System (DNS) can be used to store certificates used
to identify mail addresses.  This document describes on how to name
these certificates when stored in DNS.  This document updates RFC
2538.
	 </t>
